Welcome to '''WikiProject AI Cleanup''', a collaboration to combat the increasing problem of unsourced, poorly written [[Wikipedia:Artificial intelligence|AI-generated content on Wikipedia]]. If you would like to help, [[#Participants|add yourself as a participant]] in the project, inquire on the [[Wikipedia talk:WikiProject AI Cleanup|talk page]], and see the [[#Open tasks|to-do list]].
<!-- An optional image relating to the topic, best aligned to the right, can go here -->

* [[Wikipedia talk:Using neural network language models on Wikipedia/List of uses of ChatGPT at Wikipedia|List of uses of ChatGPT at Wikipedia]]
* [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?search=insource%3A%22chatgpt.com%22&title=Special%3ASearch&profile=advanced&fulltext=1&ns0=1 Articles using ChatGPT as a reference]
* [[Wikipedia:WikiProject AI Cleanup/AI images in non-AI contexts|AI images in non-AI contexts]]
* [[Wikipedia:Signs of AI writing]]
* [[File:Discord color D.svg|14px|link=|alt=]] [https://discord.com/invite/wikipedia AI cleanup thread in the Wikimedia discord]
* [[Wikipedia:WikiProject AI Cleanup/VWF bot log]], an automated log of images categorised as AI/upscaled on Commons which are in use on Wikipedia. It updates every Sunday, using the script at [[User:DreamRimmer/commonsfileusage.py]], and has an [[Wikipedia:WikiProject AI Cleanup/VWF bot log/Ignore|ignore list]] for AI-related articles.

